        "username": "andrew.noyes",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/andrew.noyes/{size}/443_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-01-03T22:31:38.761Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Yup, this should mostly \u201cjust work\u201d. For minimal downtime you would want to add enough machines to satisfy your desired replication policy before configuring it. You also want to add enough coordinators. This might look something like this:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Start with single ssd on one machine</li>\n<li>Add two more machines</li>\n<li>Confirm they\u2019ve joined the cluster with <code>fdbcli --exec status</code> (You should see 3 machines)</li>\n<li>\n<code>configure double ssd</code> in <code>fdbcli</code> (change config to tolerate loss of up to one machine)</li>\n<li>\n<code>coordinators auto</code> in <code>fdbcli</code> (add enough coordinators for your replication policy)</li>\n<li>Confirm fault tolerance is 1 with <code>fdbcli --exec status</code>\n</li>\n</ol>",
        "post_number": 2,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
        "updated_at": "2023-01-03T22:31:38.761Z",
